      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 1913: The URI normalization likely rejects valid bare peer IDs and may also mishandle scheme-only forms such as `jami:\u003chash\u003e` if `Uri::authority()` only returns the RFC authority component. The new public API documents `uri` as a contact URI, and callers commonly pass either a bare account ID or a `jami:` URI; returning early here makes the sync silently do nothing. Normalize with the same helper used elsewhere for Jami identifiers, or explicitly fall back to the raw/bare value when the authority is empty. Example:\n```suggestion\nauto peer \u003d Uri(uri).authority();\nif (peer.empty())\n    peer \u003d uri;\npeer \u003d jami::trim(peer);\nif (peer.empty())\n    return;\n```",
      "revId": "84766951ba94348ca4c51eb029da29733e94e7de",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
