      "writtenOn": "2026-06-22T00:06:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 1915: This loops over every conversation and starts a bootstrap for each match without any throttling or deduplication. Because this is exposed as a public libjami API, a buggy or hostile client can repeatedly trigger potentially expensive network syncs for all shared conversations with a peer. Consider reusing existing pending-fetch/bootstrap coalescing if available, or adding a small per-peer/per-conversation guard so repeated calls while a bootstrap is already in progress are ignored.",
      "revId": "84766951ba94348ca4c51eb029da29733e94e7de",
